## The Six Stages

| Stage | Name | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| 0 | Problem Definition Loop | Single dedicated agent. Only job: compress the problem statement until dense, specific, falsifiable. A cold reader must know exactly what a good solution looks like. Parliament does not activate until this passes. |
| 1 | Exploration Mode | Dynamic agent parliament. Sequential, randomised order, blind outputs — each agent writes before seeing others. |
| 2 | Crucible Synthesis | Receives all agent outputs simultaneously. Produces: tension map, convergence points, ranked conviction output with confidence levels, explicit statement of where it felt pulled. |
| 3 | Mode Switch Trigger | External contact only — customer call, prototype reaction, market data. Not a judgment call. Not a feeling. First genuine external signal flips to conviction mode. |
| 4 | Conviction Mode | Force Output Format activates. Ranked decision with confidence levels. Steelman of abandonment required — explicit case for reversing the decision before committing. |
| 5 | Human Clock | A predetermined human asks one question at a predetermined time: "Did you decide?" Not what did the Forge produce. Just — did you decide. Exists entirely outside the system's epistemology. |

