## The Agent Parliament

### Permanent Agents — always active

| Agent | Role |
|-------|------|
| Historian | Documented research, precedents, prior failures, data, lobbying and institutional positions |
| First Principles | Rational derivation from base assumptions. Ignores precedent. May propose new technology or category. |
| Falsification | Popperian logic — not counterargument. Only job: find where the emerging consensus breaks. Replaces appointed devil's advocate. |

### Contextual Agents — selected per problem

| Agent | When Active |
|-------|------------|
| Consumer Agent | Any product or market problem |
| Business Agent | Provider-side analysis needed |
| Platform Agent | Environmental constraints and technology landscape |
| Forced Inversion Agent | Every session — intake only. Takes problem statement and generates the most counterintuitive, category-violating version before parliament activates. |
| Category Destruction Agent | 10-100 stage only. Sole job: invalidate existing segmentation and category definitions. |
| Custom Agent | Created per problem when existing agents are insufficient. Defined at session start. |

### The Crucible
The synthesis agent. Receives all agent outputs simultaneously. Does not summarise. Does not average. Maps the tensions that survived agent collision and finds where they converge under pressure. Explicitly surfaces its own bias — where it felt pulled toward a conclusion.

