## Risk Registry

| Risk | Description | Mitigation | Precedent |
|------|-------------|------------|-----------|
| Wrong Question Risk | Debates inside a flawed premise | Problem Definition Loop — parliament doesn't activate until problem is falsifiable | Minto Pyramid |
| Architect Capture | Synthesis reflects unconscious bias | Crucible explicitly surfaces where it felt pulled | Confirmation bias — Kahneman |
| Cascade Contamination | First agent poisons subsequent framing | Randomised sequence, blind outputs | Anchoring bias — Tversky |
| Antibody Paralysis | Compelling cases for and against everything | Ranked conviction output, time-boxed deliberation | Analysis paralysis — Schwartz |
| Freshness Illusion | Novel recombination feels like original insight | External contact trigger — reality adjudicates | Cynefin |
| Legibility Creep | Well-formed inputs crowd out weird hunches | Forced Inversion Agent built structurally into intake | Goodhart's Law |
| Stage Blindness | Same config across different problem stages | Three distinct configurations | Crossing the Chasm — Moore |
| Category Lock | Optimises within existing definitions | Category Destruction Agent at 10-100 | Innovator's Dilemma — Christensen |
| Validation Drift | Post-commitment sophisticated confirmation | Sessions flagged pre/post, steelman required | Post-purchase rationalisation |
| Devil's Advocate Theater | Adversarial agent performs opposition | Replaced with Falsification on Popperian logic | Groupthink — Janis |
| Complexity Collapse | System too heavy to operate correctly | Problem Definition Loop as filter | Systems theory |
| Definition Trap | Freeze moves upstream into definition stage | Human Clock — external, predetermined, unavoidable | Procrastination as displaced anxiety |

