## The Four Operating Principles

Distilled from the risk registry — every mitigation is an application of one of these:

| Principle | What It Does |
|-----------|-------------|
| Disrupt default patterns | Prevents calcification — randomised sequence, rotate framing |
| Mandate uncomfortable output formats | Forces precision — ranked outputs, confidence levels, steelman |
| Build adversarial meta-agents | Structural dissent — Falsification Agent, Forced Inversion, Category Destruction |
| Force contact with reality | External trigger — mode switch, Human Clock, publish or test |

**The irreconcilable conflict:** Disrupt and Force Output Format want opposite things. Solution: they operate in different modes. Exploration uses Disrupt. Conviction uses Force Output. Never simultaneously.

