## Running The Forge

### Where It Runs
Locally on Windows PC via Claude Code. Not on Vercel.

| Component | Where | Why |
|-----------|-------|-----|
| Parliament sessions | Local — Claude Code | Long-running, expensive, needs judgment at mode switch |
| Problem Definition Loop | Local | Interactive, you're present |
| Content generation | Local | Same reason |
| Published output | Vercel | Static MDX, zero compute cost |
| Newsletter | Vercel + Resend | Lightweight, fire and forget |

Think locally. Publish globally.

### Session Workflow
1. Open Claude Code
2. State the problem
3. Run Problem Definition Loop until problem passes falsifiability test
4. Activate parliament — agents run sequentially, blind
5. Crucible synthesises
6. Await external contact for mode switch
7. Run Conviction Mode
8. Human Clock fires — did you decide?
9. Save session to `forge-sessions/YYYY-MM/`
10. If publishing → copy to `src/content/writing/` with frontmatter → push → live

